To begin in the Boston dataset

Here I have installed the ISLR2 library and from that, I have loaded the
Boston dataset into R Studio
How many rows are in the data set? How many columns? What do rows
and columns represent?
dim(Boston)
[1] 506 13
The Dataset contains 506 rows and 13 columns, Rows represent per capita
rate by town, the proportion of residential land zoned, the proportion of
residential land zoned for lots over 25,000 sq. ft, and the Charles River
dummy variable, etc.
Columns represent the data for the rows
Make some pairwise scatterplots of the predictors (columns) in the dataset

We can infer from the plots that there are more than 300 census tracts with a
crime rate of zero and only a small number with a crime rate of more than 75.
In terms of taxes, more than 160 census tracts pay 660, most pay less than
440, and only a few pay 710. 260 census tracts have a pupil-to-teacher ratio of
20; the majority of them pay less than 20 in taxes, while very few do so.
